## Hard invariants

- GC-only and ownership-aware lowering preserve the same source semantics.
- Borrow validation reads HIR and writes side tables. It does not rewrite HIR or perform backend lowering.
- Lifetime-region validation is mandatory, backend-independent and profile-independent.
- Every allocation has exactly one semantic lifetime owner.
- GC cannot bypass topology validation or legalise invalid retained edges.
- The ownership bit records destruction responsibility only.
- Backends receive validated topology and may not reconsider source legality.
- No compiler or backend path may rely on unchecked aliasing or undefined behaviour to make the ownership model work.
